description:
"Bunny Brunel & Friends - Bass Ball" Produced by Bunny Brunel & Stanley Clarke © March 2017.  (With French Subtitles)

Bassist Bunny Brunel, one of the four pioneers during the bass fusion movement, has made an impact with his melodic, dexterous playing. Bassist Stanley Clarke and Bunny Brunel formed a close friendship that has lasted over 3 decades; both virtuoso musicians have left a lasting impression on the fusion movement. This interview is the first of many to be compiled into a forthcoming feature-length documentary.  Stanley Clarke is excited to bring you sneak peaks of this exciting journey of the bass then (1970s) to its evolution through the jazz fusion movement today. 

An Agenda Pictures Production
title: Stanley Clarke Interviews Bunny Brunel (Segment 1)
